{"id": "fm3dsi", "title": "Goldman & BoA Economists Predict Record-Shattering Jobless Claims", "selftext": "https://preview.redd.it/zjx2kbzhdwn41.jpg?width=800&format=pjpg&auto=webp&s=f3a49d61afd331ab62394ccbb565543ede7f9010\n\n\"Economists at Goldman Sachs (GS) and Bank of America (BofA) have projected that initial jobless claims could top 2 million next week, up from 281,000 in the most recent report; with GS saying the number could be as high as 2.25 million and BofA forecasting that they may reach 3 million.  \n\nAt the peak of the Great Recession, jobless claims hit 665,000, and the highest number of claims previously recorded was on October 2, 1982 at 695,000.  \n\nThe projections from GS and BofA almost seem like a joke when you look at the chart over last 50 years...only they're not a joke and are reflective of the near-total shutdown of American business. \n\n[https://www.linkedin.com/posts/joseph-mayans-a3920a136\\_economics-economy-unemployment-activity-6646868792070803457-tow6](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/joseph-mayans-a3920a136_economics-economy-unemployment-activity-6646868792070803457-tow6)", "created_utc": 1584740603.0, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/fm3dsi/goldman_boa_economists_predict_recordshattering/", "is_self": true}